Enum TCardFormat

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Enum<TCardFormat>
harrygpotter.tombola.tombolalib.TCardFormat
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<TCardFormat>, java.lang.constant.Constable
public enum TCardFormat
extends java.lang.Enum<TCardFormat>
Used to specify the String format that is possible to use to visualize a card or save it in files.

1.8
Version:
1.1

    Enum Constants 
    Enum Constant Description
    AUTO
    This TCardFormat value is used specifically when reading files, to let TFileFormatter.readSeriesFile(String) try to auto-detect the format used to store the cards using meta-information provided within the header comments of the file itself.
    CSV
    Prepare a unique string containing the card label, 27 Numbers on a row (zeros in empty positions), plus the Jolly index within the [0..14] range at the end.
    CSV_PACKED
    Prepare a unique string containing the card label, 15 Numbers on a row (empty positions are skipped), plus the Jolly index within the [0..14] range at the end.
    CSV_PACKED_PLUS
    Prepare a unique string containing the card label, 15 Numbers on a row (empty positions are skipped), followed by the Jolly index within the [0..14] range and the maxEqualPerCard and maxEqualPerRow values.
    CSV_PLUS
    Prepare a unique string containing the card label, 27 Numbers on a row (zeros in empty positions), followed by the Jolly index within the [0..14] range and the maxEqualPerCard and maxEqualPerRow values.

    MSWORD_MAILMARGE
    TODO(1.2) The file aims to be ready to be used within a Microsoft Word template leveraging its "mail merge" functionalities.
    PRETTY
    The card is 'nicely' visualized on three rows, putting numbers aligned in their proper columns and leaving spaces where numbers are not present. Jolly number is enclosed in square brackets. If TCard.getExtractionCheckCount() return a value greater than zero, extracted numbers are marked within rounded brackets. If the Jolly number has been extracted, square brackets are substituted by asterisks.

    • PRETTY

      public static final TCardFormat PRETTY
      The card is 'nicely' visualized on three rows, putting numbers aligned in their proper columns and leaving spaces where numbers are not present. Jolly number is enclosed in square brackets. If TCard.getExtractionCheckCount() return a value greater than zero, extracted numbers are marked within rounded brackets. If the Jolly number has been extracted, square brackets are substituted by asterisks.

    • MSWORD_MAILMARGE

      public static final TCardFormat MSWORD_MAILMARGE
      TODO(1.2) The file aims to be ready to be used within a Microsoft Word template leveraging its "mail merge" functionalities. To achieve this goal the file has an heading line with columns (fields) names, 27 numbers for each card (so, putting zeros where there are no numbers on the matrix), no comment lines and use the real jolly number instead of its index, without brackets.
